/* EXERCICE 1 : 

Leap Year Checker: Create a function that takes a year as input and determines whether 
it is a leap year or not. Leap years are divisible by 4,
 but not by 100 unless they are also divisible by 400. */
 


 FUNCTION leap_year (A : INTEGER) : STRING
 VAR
    
 BEGIN
   
    IF ( (year MOD 4 = 0) AND (year MOD 100 <> 0 OR year MOD 400 = 0)) THEN

        RETURN "Leap year"

    ELSE

        RETURN "Not Leap year"
        
    END_IF
 
 END
 